    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"routine\" explanation, but it feels way more specific than that. like, if i'm pacing around or breathing heavy because i'm frustrated, the lights dim or the temp shifts almost instantly. it feels intentional. don't companies have the tech to analyze movement patterns or even sound/voice via these mics to detect emotional states? isn't that a massive field of research right now?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
